	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I killed him alot (before nerf), and yeah, he is weak, but the EXP was hardly worth it. The guy had a TON of HP.  Me and my best friend (level 44 rogue, and i was 43 warrior) took about 15 to 20 minutes to kill it.  About 7 to 8 kills would be 1 bubble for us. :)  If you just go near ledge and hit the key for &quot;target nearest NPC&quot;, you will target him, and I'd fire an arrow and draw him down.<BR>
<BR>
As for the entering a zone and seeing that message.  I've seen it on a few rare occasions.  I've seen it while dying from poison, or while uncounscious and then dying.  I've seen it while zoning (sometimes I would die, others I would not).  This is my theory:<BR>
<BR>
Does everyone know the bug if you are struck by a killing blow while zoning, you would actually zone and half ALOT of health left?  You know, you'd be running for your life, and then something would hit you JUST AS you zoned, enough to kill you, but you'd come out the other side with half or full health?<BR>
<BR>
Well, I think Verant &quot;fixed&quot; that (or , at least made it harder) by adding &quot;Pain and Suffering&quot;.  Basically, it would detect if this happened and then automatically put &quot;Pain and Suffering&quot; in to kill you just as/after you zone so as to compensate for the bug.<BR>
<BR>
This was a &quot;roleplay&quot; answer to the zone bug, and this NEW Pain and Suffering, I think, was just a little &quot;play&quot; on it by Verant, so as to sort of put a &quot;face&quot; to the legend.<BR>
<BR>
This is just my &quot;theory&quot;.  I dont think anything should be read into it too much, especially considering how they have made the thing 5th level. :)<BR>
<BR>
Pezz Kneecrusher<BR>

				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
