			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I believe 'twas I that first added pain and suffering to the beastiary. I was walking thru Paineel at level 29 to get my spells (I still love paineel, and it contains some rare spells like the 29th pet spell or invoke fear at 34) and i heard Pain and suffering shouts&quot;you will not escape me Jeeby&quot; (jeeby being a quite nice gnomish necro hunting him at the time) and i was like ok thats just odd. Up untill then it was assumed on my server that that platform in Paineel lead to the hole, and was unreachable thusfar. Anyway I spoke to Jeeby and he gave me a Dead man Floating and i bounced off the tree and levied up the platform. It took his group about 10 minutes per kill on the thing, which in turn respawned and came right after them every time it killed them. It doesnt resummon a runner when it says its little comment, its Pain and Suffering's dramatic version of &quot;ill teach you to interfere with me&quot; when it switches targets. Anyway i got to loot it once and all it dropped was like 1 pp, dunno if thats alot or a little for usual, only looted it once. As for !pain and suffering! i havent been back to paineel recently to validate that
				</font>
			</td>

